# ATDD Workflow

> **Authoritative procedure: [`docs/atdd/workflow.md`](../../docs/atdd/workflow.md).**
> Read that file before executing any phase. This rule is a cheatsheet, not the procedure.

## The Cycle

```
Analyze → Spec → Tests (Red) → Implementation (Green) → Quality Gates → Refactor → Spec & Doc Sync → PR
```

## Phase Map

| Phase | Name                   | Key gate / deliverable                                                |
| ----- | ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 0     | Analyze the Project    | `docs/project-profile.md` (Tooling + Conventions + Sources consulted) |
| 1     | Write the Spec         | `specs/features/*.feature` + `specs/technical/*-spec.md` — USER GATE  |
| 2     | Generate Tests (Red)   | Every scenario has a failing stub; failure is "not implemented"       |
| 3     | Implement (Green)      | Minimum code per scenario, mirroring profile; `@smoke` first          |
| 4     | Quality Gates          | Lint / format / typecheck / build / test all pass                     |
| 5     | Refactor               | Structure only, tests stay green, re-run gates                        |
| 6     | Spec & Doc Sync (Hard) | No drift: spec ↔ code ↔ tests ↔ README ↔ `docs/project-profile.md`    |
| 7     | PR (optional)          | Feature branch, commit, push; include scenario summary                |

## Hard Gates

- **Phase 1 → 2**: explicit user approval of the spec. Iterate until approved.
- **Phase 2 → 3**: all tests red for the right reason. Print test runner output.
- **Phase 6 → done**: repair drift in-phase. Do not defer spec / README / profile updates.

## Before Phase 3

Always:

1. Re-read `docs/project-profile.md` (`Conventions`, `Reference Files`, `Anti-patterns`).
2. Open at least one reference file from the same layer you're about to write.
3. State explicitly which conventions you will follow.

## Spec Change Protocol

Spec → tests → code → `README.md` → `docs/project-profile.md` (if conventions changed). In that
order. Doc updates are part of the change, not a follow-up. Full protocol:
`docs/atdd/workflow.md` § Spec Change Protocol.
